appearances.title: Washington Journal Washington Journal : CSPAN : January 1, 2026 10:03am-1:28pm EST
appearances.snippet: representative randy feenstra who was elected to congress from the northwest part of iowa.here is a lot of animosity toward him in republican circles and he has been running a quiet campaign. he is avoiding open public meetings and multi-candidate forums and a lot of republicans are not happy about that so i think the governor's race will be competitive. probably even more so than the senate race because we have seen in other states like kansas and kentucky and louisiana that we have seen even republican leaning states elect democrats as governor more often than we have seen them elect democrats to u.s. senate. host: you have randy feenstra running for government, ashley hinson running for senator, leaving two of the four congressional house seats open. how likely is it that some of the seats become the battleground seats that determine control of the u.s. house in 2026? guest: one interesting thing about iowa as we do not have gerrymandering. we have four u.s. house districts and almost every cycle at least two of them are competitive so even before any of the reshuffling
